{
  "id": "RAW_a7a90bab",
  "title": "TOON：通过减少令牌消耗优化 LLM 成本",
  "url": "https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/11/toon-reduce-llm-cost-tokens/?utm_campaign=infoq_content&utm_source=infoq&utm_medium=feed&utm_term=global",
  "date": "2025-11-23 02:49:00",
  "author": "Bruno Couriol",
  "siteName": "InfoQ",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div class=\"article__data\">\n   <p>The recently released <a href=\"https://github.com/toon-format/toon\">Token-Oriented Object Notation (TOON)</a> aims to be a schema-aware alternative to JSON that significantly reduces token consumption at a similar level of accuracy. While the existence and quantity of saved tokens depend on the data shape, some benchmarks show that TOON may use 40% fewer tokens in some cases than JSON, potentially resulting in LLM and inference cost savings.</p>\n   <p>TOON self-describes as a compact, human-readable encoding of the JSON data model for LLM prompts.</p>\n   <p>Consider the following JSON:</p>\n   <pre class=\"language-json\">\r\n<code class=\"prism  language-json\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\r\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"context\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\r\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"task\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Our favorite hikes together\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"location\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Boulder\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"season\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"spring_2025\"</span>\r\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"friends\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"ana\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"luis\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"sam\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"hikes\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\r\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"id\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"name\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Blue Lake Trail\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"distanceKm\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">7.5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"elevationGain\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">320</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"companion\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"ana\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"wasSunny\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span>\r\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"id\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"name\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Ridge Overlook\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"distanceKm\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">9.2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"elevationGain\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">540</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"companion\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"luis\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"wasSunny\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">false</span>\r\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"id\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"name\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Wildflower Loop\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"distanceKm\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">5.1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"elevationGain\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">180</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"companion\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"sam\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\r\n      <span class=\"token string\">\"wasSunny\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span>\r\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\r\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\r\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\r\n</code></pre>\n   <p>In the TOON format, the same data becomes:</p>\n   <pre class=\"language-csv\">\r\n<code class=\"prism  language-csv\">context:\r\n  task: Our favorite hikes together\r\n  location: Boulder\r\n  season: spring_2025\r\n\r\nfriends[3]: ana,luis,sam\r\n\r\nhikes[3]{id,name,distanceKm,elevationGain,companion,wasSunny}:\r\n  1,Blue Lake Trail,7.5,320,ana,true\r\n  2,Ridge Overlook,9.2,540,luis,false\r\n  3,Wildflower Loop,5.1,180,sam,true\r\n</code></pre>\n   <p><a href=\"https://www.curiouslychase.com/playground/format-tokenization-exploration?mode=custom&amp;data=%257B%250A%2520%2520%2522context%2522%253A%2520%257B%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522task%2522%253A%2520%2522Our%2520favorite%2520hikes%2520together%2522%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522location%2522%253A%2520%2522Boulder%2522%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522season%2522%253A%2520%2522spring_2025%2522%250A%2520%2520%257D%252C%250A%2520%2520%2522friends%2522%253A%2520%255B%2522ana%2522%252C%2520%2522luis%2522%252C%2520%2522sam%2522%255D%252C%250A%2520%2520%2522hikes%2522%253A%2520%255B%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%257B%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522id%2522%253A%25201%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522name%2522%253A%2520%2522Blue%2520Lake%2520Trail%2522%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522distanceKm%2522%253A%25207.5%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522elevationGain%2522%253A%2520320%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522companion%2522%253A%2520%2522ana%2522%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522wasSunny%2522%253A%2520true%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%257D%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%257B%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522id%2522%253A%25202%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522name%2522%253A%2520%2522Ridge%2520Overlook%2522%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522distanceKm%2522%253A%25209.2%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522elevationGain%2522%253A%2520540%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522companion%2522%253A%2520%2522luis%2522%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522wasSunny%2522%253A%2520false%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%257D%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%257B%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522id%2522%253A%25203%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522name%2522%253A%2520%2522Wildflower%2520Loop%2522%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522distanceKm%2522%253A%25205.1%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522elevationGain%2522%253A%2520180%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522companion%2522%253A%2520%2522sam%2522%252C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2520%2522wasSunny%2522%253A%2520true%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520%257D%250A%2520%2520%255D%250A%257D\">Running this example in an online playground</a> will show a 55% reduction in tokens vs. pretty-printed JSON, 25% vs. compact JSON, and 38% vs. YAML.</p>\n   <p>&nbsp;</p>\n   <p><img alt=\"\" style=\"width:100%;height:541px;\" data-src=\"https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/11/toon-reduce-llm-cost-tokens/news/2025/11/toon-reduce-llm-cost-tokens/en/resources/1toon-1763863763963.png\" src=\"https://imgopt.infoq.com/fit-in/3000x4000/filters:quality(85)/filters:no_upscale()/news/2025/11/toon-reduce-llm-cost-tokens/en/resources/1toon-1763863763963.png\" rel=\"share\"></p>\n   <p>As the previous example showcases, TOON combines YAML (for nested objects) and CSV (for uniform arrays) layouts to save tokens. However, for non-uniform data, <a href=\"https://www.curiouslychase.com/playground/format-tokenization-exploration?mode=preset&amp;size=large-complex&amp;structure=non-uniform-flat\">JSON may be more efficient</a>. For deeply nested objects, YAML <a href=\"https://www.curiouslychase.com/playground/format-tokenization-exploration?mode=preset&amp;size=large-complex&amp;structure=uniform-nested-uniform\">may be more token-efficient</a>. For flat datasets, CSV remains the most compact format. TOON adds a small overhead (~5%) with field headers and array declarations, in order to improve LLM accuracy.</p>\n   <p><a href=\"https://x.com/jschopplich\">Johann Schopplich</a> <a href=\"https://x.com/jschopplich/status/1982831991029633110\">explained on X</a>:</p>\n   <blockquote>\n    <p>“Does token efficiency hurt accuracy?”\n     <br>\n     No :) TOON hits 99.4% accuracy on GPT 5 Nano while using 46% fewer tokens.\n     <br>\n     Tested across ~160 questions and 3 LLMs with semantic validation.\n     <br>\n     I think explicit lengths + field lists = fewer mistakes.</p>\n   </blockquote>\n   <p>Readers may review <a href=\"https://github.com/toon-format/spec\">TOON’s specifications</a>, <a href=\"https://toonformat.dev/guide/llm-prompts\">documentation</a>, <a href=\"https://www.curiouslychase.com/playground/format-tokenization-exploration?mode=preset&amp;size=large-complex&amp;structure=non-uniform-flat\">online playgrounds</a>, and <a href=\"https://github.com/toon-format/toon/tree/main/benchmarks\">run their own efficiency and accuracy benchmarks</a>. In latency-critical applications, developers should compare Time To First Token and tokens per second in both formats.</p>\n   <p>The reference implementation in TypeScript/JavaScript is maintained at <a href=\"https://github.com/toon-format/toon\">github.com/toon-format/toon</a>. The reference implementation includes a complete encoder and decoder, CLI tools for JSON-to-TOON conversion, and performance benchmarks. TOON 1.0 was released under the MIT license two weeks ago.</p>\n  </div>\n  <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"\" value=\"Thank you for your review!\" id=\"cr_messages_submitSuccess\"> <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"\" value=\"Rating is required\" id=\"cr_messages_ratingRequired\"> <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"\" value=\"New Token-Oriented Object Notation (TOON) Hopes to Cut LLM Costs by Reducing Token Consumption\" id=\"cr_item_title\"> <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"\" value=\"Bruno Couriol\" id=\"cr_item_author\"> <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"\" value=\"http://www.infoq.com/news/2025/11/toon-reduce-llm-cost-tokens/\" id=\"cr_item_url\"> <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"\" value=\"news\" id=\"cr_item_ctype\"> <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"\" value=\"en\" id=\"cr_item_lang\"> <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"\" value=\"1763866140000\" id=\"cr_item_published_time\"> <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"\" value=\"2497\" id=\"cr_item_primary_topic\">\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "TOON (面向令牌的对象表示法) 是一种新型的、感知模式的 JSON 替代方案，旨在显著减少 LLM 提示中的令牌消耗，从而潜在地节省成本并实现类似的准确性。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "TOON (面向令牌的对象表示法) 是一种新型的、感知模式的 JSON 替代方案，旨在显著减少 LLM 提示中的令牌消耗，从而潜在地节省成本并实现类似的准确性。",
  "summary": "本文介绍了面向令牌的对象表示法 (TOON)，这是一种新发布的数据格式，旨在通过减少令牌使用量，优化 LLM 提示效率，相较于 JSON 有显著提升。TOON 被描述为 JSON 数据模型的紧凑、人类可读的编码，它结合了 YAML 用于嵌套对象和 CSV 用于统一数组的元素。基准测试表明，在某些情况下，TOON 可以减少 40-55% 的令牌消耗，从而可能降低 LLM 推理成本。本文提供了具体的示例，比较了相同数据的 JSON 和 TOON 格式，说明了令牌节省的情况。它还解决了准确性的问题，引用了测试表明 TOON 在 GPT 5 Nano 上实现了 99.4% 的准确率，同时使用了减少 46% 的令牌，这归因于显式的长度和字段列表。虽然对于结构化数据来说很有效，但文章指出 JSON 或 YAML 可能更适合非统一或深度嵌套的对象。TOON 是一个开源项目，提供规范、文档、在线试验场以及在 MIT 许可证下发布的 TypeScript/JavaScript 参考实现，使其易于开发人员探索和进行基准测试。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "TOON 显著降低 LLM 提示的令牌消耗，优于 JSON。",
      "explanation": "TOON 结合 YAML 和 CSV 结构，在基准测试中实现了 40-55% 的令牌减少，从而直接降低 LLM 推理成本。"
    },
    {
      "point": "TOON 在减少令牌的同时保持高准确率，消除了对数据完整性的疑虑。",
      "explanation": "测试显示，即使使用更少的令牌，TOON 在 GPT 5 Nano 上仍然达到了 99.4% 的准确率，这说明显式的模式信息有助于 LLM 的理解。"
    },
    {
      "point": "TOON 效率受数据形态影响，实施需谨慎评估。",
